      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 245: onAudioCongestion() does not validate non-finite or out-of-range audioLoss, while update() explicitly protects its EWMA state from invalid samples. A NaN audio loss bypasses the threshold check and still reduces video bitrate; very large values can also force aggressive reductions based on bad input. Apply the same input validation/clamping here before making control decisions.\n```suggestion\n    if (!std::isfinite(audioLoss))\n        return targetBitrate_;\n\n    audioLoss \u003d std::clamp(audioLoss, 0.0f, 100.0f);\n\n    // Ignore if below threshold\n    if (audioLoss \u003c cfg_.audioLossThreshold)\n        return targetBitrate_;\n```",
