      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 289: REMB overuse decreases do not preserve the pre-congestion bitrate in lastStableBitrate_, unlike applyDecrease() and onAudioCongestion(). After a REMB-triggered drop from a high bitrate, recovery is throttled against a stale/default lastStableBitrate_ value, so video can recover much more slowly than intended. Mirror the stable-bitrate update used by the other decrease paths before applying the REMB reduction.\n```suggestion\n        if (state_ !\u003d State::Draining)\n            lastStableBitrate_ \u003d targetBitrate_;\n\n        auto oldBitrate \u003d targetBitrate_;\n        targetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(static_cast\u003cunsigned\u003e(std::lround(static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(targetBitrate_) * 0.85f)));\n```",
      "revId": "784e4d2425dc5ddaa3089465d22ec76b17a4fd3b",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
