      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 654: Normal REMB feedback is now passed to onRembFeedback(false), but that method intentionally does not increase bitrate. This removes the previous delay-based increase path, so if RR stats are unavailable or skipped, a stream reduced by REMB/audio congestion can remain stuck until another RR update arrives. Either let normal REMB advance the controller\u0027s probing path, or explicitly document and enforce RR as the sole increase signal.\n```suggestion\n            auto newBitrate \u003d isOveruse\n                ? bwController_.onRembFeedback(true)\n                : bwController_.update(0.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f);\n            setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n```",
